## 2026-03-28 - Inline theme editing in token editor
- Added a "Theme values" collapsible section to `TokenEditor.tsx` that appears when editing a token with theme dimensions configured. For each dimension × option, shows the current raw value from the appropriate theme set (perSetFlat), with inline text editing for simple types (color, string, number, dimension, duration, boolean, fontFamily, fontWeight). Complex/composite types show read-only "overridden/inherited" status. Alias values show read-only token reference path. Each editable row has a "Save" button that PATCHes the target set directly and calls `onRefresh` to stay in the editor. Added `perSetFlat` and `onRefresh` props to `TokenEditorProps` and passed them from both TokenEditor usage sites in App.tsx.
- Files changed: `packages/figma-plugin/src/ui/components/TokenEditor.tsx` ~L142 (ThemeValuesSection component), ~L330 (new props), ~L1165 (render call); `packages/figma-plugin/src/ui/App.tsx` ~L2173, ~L2464 (prop passing)
- **Learnings for future iterations:**

