## 2026-03-28 - Search qualifier discoverability: autocomplete, placeholder hints, filter dropdown
- Extended qualifier autocomplete with value completion: typing `type:` now shows all token types from the current set; typing `has:` shows all recognized has: values (alias, direct, duplicate, description, extension). Partial prefixes filter the list (e.g. `type:co` → `type:color`).
- Added discovery mode: focusing an empty search field now shows all available qualifiers in the autocomplete dropdown with a "Search qualifiers" header, so new users can discover the qualifier syntax without pressing `?`.
- Moved `qualifierHints` useMemo to after `availableTypes` declaration to fix a potential TDZ crash (per codebase patterns).

